><br />Which is why you get a full pathname even when you only opened<br />something using a relative pathname.<br /><br />So the fact that we _don't_ get the right pathname for the pts entry<br />here means that something got screwed up in setting filp-&gt;f_path to<br />the right thing. We have all the code in place that _tries_ to do it,<br />but it clearly has a bug somewhere.<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
